    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's hard to find comfort in \"shared experiences\" when the experience is just watching everything we love get destroyed. honestly, it feels less like a problem to cope with and more like a fundamental truth. if the world is genuinely ending, then why stay for the wreckage? why keep putting yourself through the stress and the pain of living if there isn't a real future to live for? it almost feels more logical to just opt out now than to suffer through the collapse.",
